{"article_id":"s9ZjyvwEua7Z0JkR","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"HONG KONG","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"( AP ) -","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam announced Wednesday","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"the government will formally withdraw an extradition bill","depth":12},{"id":4,"text":"that sparked months of demonstrations ,","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"bowing to one of the protesters ' demands in the hope","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"of ending the increasingly violent unrest .","depth":12},{"id":7,"text":"But lawmakers warned","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that the bill ' s withdrawal was not enough","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"to end the turmoil ,","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"which has increasingly focused on alleged police brutality against protesters and democratic reforms .","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"The bill would have allowed Hong Kong residents to be sent to mainland China for trials .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"It has prompted massive protests since June","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that disrupted transport links","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and caused the airport to shut down earlier this month .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Lam said","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"the government would not accept other demands","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"including an independent inquiry into alleged police misconduct and the unconditional release of those detained .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Instead , she named two new members to a police watchdog agency","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"investigating the matter .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"\" The government will formally withdraw the bill","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"in order to fully allay public concerns , \"","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"she said in a recorded television message .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"She said","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"the persistent violence is damaging the rule of law","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"and that moves","depth":14},{"id":26,"text":"to vandalize the national flag and emblem","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"were a direct challenge to the \" one country , two systems \" policy","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"and had put Hong Kong in a \" highly vulnerable and dangerous situation . \"","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"\" Our foremost priority now is to end violence ,","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"to safeguard the rule of law","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"and to restore order and safety in society , \"","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"she added ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"vowing to \" strictly enforce the law against all violent and illegal acts . \"","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Lam said","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"it was clear that public frustration has gone far beyond the bill","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"and that her government will seek a dialogue with aggrieved groups","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"to \" address the discontent in society","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"and to look for solutions . \"","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"She said","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"she will also invite community leaders , professionals and academics","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"to examine deep-seated problems in the society","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"and advise the government on solutions .","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"\" Let ' s replace conflicts with conversations ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"and let ' s look for solutions , \"","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Lam made the announcement","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"after meeting with pro-government lawmakers and members of the National People ' s Congress and the Chinese People ' s Political Consultative Conference .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Lawmaker Michael Tien ,","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"who was at the meeting ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"the move would not change public sentiment","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"if it isn ' t accompanied by other concessions .","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"\" It is too little , too late .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"The focus now has completely shifted .","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"Most people do not remember what the bill is about","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"but are more concerned about the escalating violence and alleged police heavy-handedness against protesters , \"","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Lam rejected his call during the meeting for an independent inquiry","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"which would have the power","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"to summon witnesses ,","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"on the ground","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"that it would overlap with the police watchdog probe .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Pro-democracy lawmaker Claudia Mo said","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"the protesters are adamant","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"that all their demands ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"including calls for direct elections ,","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"are fulfilled .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"She mocked Lam ' s bid","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"to seek dialogue","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"to address public grievances .","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"\" She has been fast asleep these three months ,","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"this is just absurd , \"","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"Mo said .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"\" The scars and wounds are still bleeding ,","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"and she thinks","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"she can just use some garden hose","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"to put out the hill fire .","depth":16},{"id":79,"text":"That is not acceptable . \"","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Pro-establishment lawmaker Starry Lee , however , urged protesters to accept the government ' s olive branch","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"so the city can move forward .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"The Hong Kong stock market soared 4 % ,","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"boosted by reports of the bill ' s withdrawal .","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"Lam has come under withering criticism","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"for pushing the extradition bill ,","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"which many in Hong Kong see as an example of the city ' s eroding autonomy","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"since the former British colony returned to Chinese control in 1997 .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"She was elected as Hong Kong ' s chief executive by a pro-Beijing committee of Hong Kong elites ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"and the mainland government has spoken in support of her government and the city ' s police force throughout the protests .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Clashes between police and protesters have become increasingly violent ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"with demonstrators throwing gasoline bombs and rods at officers in protests last weekend .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Authorities in turn have employed water cannons , tear gas , rubber bullets and batons .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"More than 1,100 people have been detained .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"The mostly young protesters say","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that a degree of violence is necessary","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"to get the government ' s attention","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"after peaceful rallies were futile .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"In Beijing , the mainland office","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"responsible for Hong Kong","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"has warned","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"that China will \" not sit idly by \"","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"if the situation worsens .","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"The prolonged protests have hurt Hong Kong ' s economy amid a slowdown in the Chinese economy and its trade war with the United States .","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"Hong Kong and foreign companies have also been under intense pressure","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"to support China ' s ruling Communist Party against the protesters .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"The chairman of Hong Kong ' s Cathay Pacific Airways resigned Wednesday ,","depth":5},{"id":107,"text":"becoming the second top figure","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"to leave the airline","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"since the protests erupted .","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"Cathay said","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"John Slosar was retiring from the airline , one of Hong Kong ' s most prominent businesses .","depth":5},{"id":112,"text":"It comes","depth":4},{"id":113,"text":"less than one month after Cathay ' s CEO , Rupert Hogg , resigned","depth":5},{"id":114,"text":"following pressure by Beijing over participation by some of the carrier ' s employees in protests .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":229,"left":0,"right":228,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":228,"left":219,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":197,"right":218,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":195,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":128,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":1,"right":127,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":124,"right":126,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":119,"right":122,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":119,"left":2,"right":118,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":118,"left":116,"right":117,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":7,"right":121,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":121,"left":8,"right":120,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":12,"right":125,"relation":"elab